# KURA LIVE - Kenya Election 2027 MVP Development Rules

## Technology Stack
- Stack: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript strict mode, Tailwind CSS
- Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL) with client library
- Auth: Supabase Auth with middleware protection
- State: Zustand
- Forms: React Hook Form + Zod validation
- Icons: Lucide React
- Charts: Recharts
- Animations: Framer Motion
- Video: react-player
- Deployment: Vercel

## Code Standards
- Never use 'any' TypeScript type
- All components are named exports, never default exports for components
- All API routes follow RESTful conventions and return { data, error } shape
- Database: all queries go through /lib/supabase.ts client
- All user-facing errors are caught and displayed in toast notifications
- Auth: use middleware.ts to protect /dashboard and /admin routes
- Never use inline styles — always Tailwind classes
- Mobile-first responsive design on all components
- All async operations show loading states

## Project Structure
src/
app/
├── page.tsx -- Landing/login redirect
├── login/page.tsx -- Agent login page
├── dashboard/
│   ├── page.tsx -- Main dashboard (tabs: Stream | Transcription | Results | Comparison | Alerts)
│   └── layout.tsx -- Protected layout with nav
├── admin/
│   ├── page.tsx -- Campaign admin panel
│   └── layout.tsx -- Admin-protected layout
├── results/page.tsx -- Public results dashboard (no auth)
└── api/
    ├── streams/route.ts -- GET/POST live streams
    ├── tallies/route.ts -- GET/POST tally entries
    ├── tallies/[station]/route.ts -- GET tallies by station
    ├── forms/route.ts -- POST form upload metadata
    ├── alerts/route.ts -- GET/POST/PATCH alerts
    ├── iebc/[station]/route.ts -- GET mock IEBC portal data
    └── simulate/transcript/route.ts -- POST simulate transcription

components/
├── ui/ -- Core UI components (Badge, StatCard, AlertCard, etc.)
├── dashboard/ -- Dashboard panels
└── public/ -- Public-facing components

lib/
├── supabase.ts -- Supabase client (server + client versions)
├── supabase-server.ts -- Server-side Supabase client
├── types.ts -- TypeScript interfaces
├── constants.ts -- App constants
└── demo-data.ts -- Mock/demo data

hooks/ -- Custom React hooks
store/ -- Zustand stores

